caption: I like this spot! They give superb food, their menu is nice, The cook in that spot is very experienced, I enjoy a lot eating all their dishes. The food is always tasty, the attitude towards the customers  is good. I visit often this restaurant and I was never disappointed. Highly recommended.
This place is worth a try. They serve large portions for fair rates. Regularly well organized and with good atmosphere. Will come visit again.

Just like in Alsace! I’m happy I have finally found a place with the real tartes flambées and the traditional “spaetzle” pasta. The atmosphere is very authentic as well! I love to sit outside or next to the chimney!

Our favorite spot in the neighborhood. Good food and their specials are always a great choice. They keep the drinks menu interesting too with a changing list of craft cocktails. Cozy in the winter with a fireplace and comfy in the summer on the terrace overlooking Union street’s brownstones.
Incredible French-German dishes and comfy and warm outdoor dining setup. Try the wine and Onion Soup!

One of the best (and prettiest) burgers in town, and top notch french fare: the onion soup and Camembert Roti are really tasty. The outside pods are comfy and a given, in these covid-stricken times! Staff polite and helpfull. Also great drinks, specially mulled wine is great in the winter.
Delicious and generous portions served in super cozy heated socially distanced huts. Thank you!

We like a lot going out. Yesterday we came to this delicious restaurant which friends recommended to us. We passed a lovely experience there with excellent dishes and an efficient stuff and an impressive cook. We  added this venue in our list  and we will certainly come back very soon. We highly recommend.
Food is disgusting
Very bad food and service
I regularly come buying some food in here. I liked the fast service and well made food. 5 stars from me.
This place simply knows how to treat their customers. Constantly with a very friendly attitude. The food is conveniently priced, regularly tasty and clean.
Great Food at reasonable prices. First time delivery ordered Steak Frites and French Onion Soup.  Really happy and will definitely order again.
Great service

Not good at all. I ordered an appetizer and main dish. The salad was terrible. Quality of ingredients are questionable. Main dish was blend and tasteless. Do not recommend this place. Avoid this spot.
Food doesn't respond to the price
Great food, great service! Nice atmosphere. We were there on a Saturday night and they had live music.
Very good food, pleasant staff and cozy atmosphere! New favorite place in Brooklyn. Baked Brie cheese was 😋
Great food, friendly staff, nice setting. Definitely recommend!
Excellent Food.  Good service.  Nice atmosphere.
This spot never fails to deliver. They serve fantastic dishes for fair prices, there no long wait even when the spot is packed.
Best French onion soup that I've ever had
Everything from the service to the food is great. I recommend trying my favorite drink "morning at Dawn".
Great food and vibe. The outdoor seating is wonderful as well.

This site is my first choice site.  Of all restaurants I know I like it most. I never miss an opportunity to go to this restaurant. everytime  I I need a special lunchon, this is the place that comes immediately to my head. splendid and many types of  food and a rich menu.great team, and nice ambience. And very important, the cost is reasonable. I tell about this restaurant with great pleasure.
Great outdoor dining experience — food was pretty good l, but not great & the staff were wonderful
Real #Alsacian #flammekueche 🙌 so good

My husband randomly took me here after taking me for dessert at The Brooklyn Farmacy (we were still hungry.) I have to say the cheese board here is definitely one of the best I’ve had so far here in NYC, and the tuna tartare was spot on. I was hoping to try the steak tartare but unfortunately, it was not available at the time we went. Overall the ambience is great, especially with the outdoor seating. I definitely will be coming back!
I constantly come grabbing some food in this spot. I loved the rapid customer service and well prepared dishes. Fantastic work.
This spot is awesome! Fair pricing, large portions and the employees are consistently friendly.
(Translated by Google) Come to see your report on France 2 I wish you good luck  (Original) Viens de voir votre reportage sur France 2 je vous souhaite bon courage
(Translated by Google) Unpleasant welcome, average cuisine lacks provenance information  (Original) Accueil désagréable, cuisine moyenne manque de renseignements sur la provenance
Good ambiance. And good flatbread
Surely a place worth visiting, the food is fantastic and fresh, the pricing is affordable and it is constantly well organized here. Highly recommended.
Best restaurant in Carroll Gardens
I had an awesome time at this spot. We enjoyed the fantastic environment and the food. The staff members are very affable. I am happy we ultimately decided to visit this spot.
lot of space, excellent food (and drinks) and cute! All these criteria dont come often together 😍
Delicious food, nice setting (if a little loud)

I went to La Cigogne last night with a party of 8 and I must say that the food and service was amazing. They have a live band on Saturdays which brings a really good vibe to the restaurant. I heard the brunch is really good too which I am looking forward to trying out in the near future.
Great environment and unique quinine. Love this place.
Very cosy. Nice ambiance. Menu serving could be a little bit better
French food with alcesian touch. Great for families. Ambiance is Cousy. Service is great.
Staff is so friendly and food is excellent!
Food was very bad. No one cared that I asked for my check after one bite of each dish.
Was so good! We went back twice in the same weekend because we loved it so much. There’s a cute and romantic vibe there, loved it!
This place is excellent! Reasonable rates, big portions and the staff members are constantly super nice.
Delicious
Excellent food and the place is beautiful
Had a excellent experience in this spot with my friend. The food came fast and the customer service is just fantastic. Prices are fair.
This is place is good, polite staff and food is delicious. Ordered salad and french onion soup and ate it all.  If you around and hungry, this is the place.

Super kid-friendly small restaurant that accommodated all of our needs having 4 children under 4 there.  They had kids books and a changing table and the servers were friendly and attentive. The food was awesome and the vibe was chill and unique. Wedtotally go again if we lived closer.  The tuna tartare was amazing and we enjoyed the brussel sprouts. The salads were delicately dressed and the mac and cheese was a crowd pleaser.
Great food.
They only had one type of chardonnay and it was only fair. Coupled with a tiny poor we were disappointed.
Food was excellent, really nice portion on the fish dish I ordered with fresh bright veggies!
Delicious food, great service. Very nice atmosphere.
Food is meh
Fantastic cocktails and food! Really enjoyed Le Burger.

The chicken mousse with cranberries was excellent. Ratatouille was great. Drinks menu has several spectacular cocktails. My recommendation is the clouded one. The $2 add-on for bacon in your pasta is totally worth it.
Great food, service was a little slow.  I had the Smoked Salmon bene which was very tasty, but someone at my table ordered the spaetzl and I was very jealous.
The food was quite good and so was service.
Great flatbreads and cocktails in a very cozy environment. Really enjoyed my meal here.
One of our favorite restaurants in Carroll Gardens.  Always have football (soccer) matches

Had a party of 15. Service was slow, about 20 minutes for drinks to get to the table? Some appetizers were good, the clams were however half missing from the shells strangley. Entree was TERRIBLE. 3 of us ordered the filet mignon and it was definitely not a filet. Worst steak I've ever  eaten. Very jelly and chewy, did not melt like a filet should've... I will not come back here.  Also I don't leave reviews often, so the fact I am ranting about this one, it is really that bad and overrated....  The manager was nice but overall a very negative experience.

With a roaring fire in the background, you can have classic French dishes like escargot, onion soup as well as steak frites. The thing they have that is a bit more rare on the menus of countless French bistros in NYC, are their Germanic dishes from Alsace which are perfect for a cold evening- spaetzle, schnitzel among other things. What's even better is that they do wine and beer very very well.
One of the best french restaurant in town. Mr Damien the manager is a nice guy. Les mets sont un délice.
It's our top 5 in the neighborhood .... very cozy, great service, diverse menu, great drinks, absolutely delicious food, and reasonably priced.
The service and atmosphere were lovely, and the steak was cooked to the requested level of doneness, but the spatzle was relatively bland.
Neighborhoodie
Cozy atmosphere with good food, good drinks and a roaring fireplace. Always a solid choice.
Very nice date spot
Delicious scallops and fries. My pasta dish was okay, but not so memorable. Not thrilled with the wait service.
Fun spot. Tasty breakfast pizza.

Huge promise but feels like a work in progress. Slow kitchen and some issues with mains.  Food was extremely slow on a relatively quiet Sunday evening, we waited close to 45 mins between appetisers and mains.  The Tarte Flambee was nice but it's a shame they put crispy bacon on there instead fresh lardons.  Many reviews note that steaks we're overcooked. Our medium burger arrived close to well done so it seems like a common problem.  Pros: free bread course was delicious. Staff were lovely. Atmosphere and décor is super cosy, I enjoyed the vibe.
Nice cozy place with pleasant service and tasty food
Great atmosphere, great food! We’ll definitely come back!!
Amazing food
C'est good stuff. I had the chicken, brussel sprouts, and tuna tartare. You would do well with all of the above.
Lovely atmosphere and great service to compliment some great Alsatian food.

Alsatian food in Carroll Gardens.  Something I wasn't expecting, but was glad to find.  I went with my family, and we were very pleased.  I had the kari (curry) spaetzle, which was very good -- and I love spaetzle.  My daughter got the steak frites, which was also quite good.  My wife got a special, the braised short rib, and that ranged up toward excellent.  The beer selection was also very good.  If you're an Alsatian place and you can't get beer right, well, that would be a miss.  About the only issue was with the service.  It was extremely friendly, but dishes were mixed up or forgotten, and everything went slowly.  Still, put it on your Franco-German food map.
Fireplace and ambience is romantic, but not cheesy. Perfect for a date night.

Very tasty! I had the spetzl (?), which was a fresh pasta in cream sauce, with a wonderfully complex and balanced mix of flavors. The portion size was pretty large, so I didn't get to try the sides this time.  But I'll be going back!
Slow service, brought appetizer with meal. Food was like warm.

Service was great, food was very good. Restaurant has books for kids to read at the table. Owner was on the floor getting drinks and talking with the customers. Will definitely be back to this great restaurant.
Have had good and not good food experiences.  Inconsistency.  3 or 4 stars is most common.
Over cooked burger, burnt bun, took an exceedingly long time for our food too come out. It would be one star but the wait staff was very good.
I really didn't like the food and the service
Fresh food, excellent service and ambiance, very fair pricing, great wine selection, friendly staff-- what more do you want? Go, and enjoy!!
Solid French bistro with a focus on the Alsace Lorraine region.

Wait staff and atmosphere was nice and accommodating of our kids, but the service was extremely slow, and half our food was very overcooked. The place was near empty. The other dishes were fine, but unremarkable. I never leave bad reviews, but this time I must.
OK overall. Usually a long wait, even when the restaurant is empty.
Couldn't be better.  Excellent cocktails, amazing staff, extraordinary food.  Can't recommend it enough.
Good Food, terrible service, the size of the type on the menu is microscopic, but if you can deal with waiting for 45 minutes + for your meal and never see your waiter it’s a good value.
Went there to watch France vs Argentina. Good food and ambience with reasonable price. Will most probably return for the next round match.
Nice atmosphere
Decent alsatian food. The spaetzle and the tarte flambee both could have used a bit more of a flavor profile though.

Excellent all round. Ended up here on my wait for Lucalli. This place is much better and the drinks and food were top notch.  Actually some of the best I found in NYC.  A little out the way but if you have to be in the area. I strongly recommend a stop by.

Great cocktails, friendly service, but mediocre food. My wife and I had excellent cocktails and a meat and cheese board, but our curried mussels lacked flavor and were overly salted. The mushroom flat bread we ordered had no real flavor besides the bacon and used uncut Enokitake mushrooms that were stringy, and very difficult to chew. We each ate two bites before politely telling the waiter we didn't like it. He apologized, was very polite, and did not make any adjustments to the check. It's a great neighborhood bar and we'll be back for drinks and apps, but will probably pass on another seated dinner.
Love this place for great ambience. Cocktails and food are awesome!
Lovely neighborhood French restaurant with good food, service and atmosphere.

This place was very good. The waiters were extremely friendly, very helpful, and they gave great suggestions on the cocktails and menu items. Everything we had was great. Two cocktails and two entrees came out to about 75 (including tip). Its worth the price, and a fantastically romantic atmosphere.
Terrible slow service. Never bring kids. They will be crying .
Awesome place, awesome food, awesome drinks!!! What else you need? 👌🏻👍🏻😊
Service was rather slow but the food and ambience were quite good.
Good brunch and can accommodate large parties.
Had the Squid Ink Spatzle and the salmon dish and both were amazing. At ~20 bucks each I’ll be stopping by more often to try more dishes.
Such a pretty place with fancy cocktails
$$$$, but well worth it

Never had this type of French food before. A friend of mine invited me to this place because he's from this region of France. He explained how authentic their food is to the region of France he lived which borders this region. Definitely quite the experience going to this placing and learning about the area and their style. I tried one of the spatzle, it's a pasta with tomato based sauce, beets and corn. It was tasty. They give you a good amount so come hungry. I also tried a piece of one of their flambee. Delectable. Their service is pretty good. The waiter checked on us a few times without being intrusive. It's a lovely place to have a dinner on the patio especially on a late summer night or a day. I'll definitely come back.
Great
Chill!
Good food service and the whole shebang

Great french restaurant. Great service, awesome cocktails and over all just a lovely place. Food is obviously great, Les tartes flambées are just amazing (Les champignons is the best...for me). Sadly the bar tender is a Marseille soccer team fan...nobody is perfect I know, but he is still such a fun person and a great cocktail maker.
The food was amazing, the drinks were wonderful and the apple crumble a la mode was the perfect end to a great dinner! Would definitely recommend this place.
Nice hideaway, with a very traditional French menu

Have had dinner at La Cigogne many times.  Love their food and atmosphere.  Price is not expensive and service is good.  When you arrive, show your Yelp check in to the waiter and you will get free beer flight.
Great place that is cozy and has decent food and cocktails.
Super Alsatian food!

A romantic and cozy local spot with great food (the mussels marinier and Le Burger we're nice and really delicious), amazing bread and very decent cocktails and wine list! The service also is very attentive and fast. Also it is quite spacious so you don't feel claustrophobic like in many nice Brooklyn restaurants.

This place is great for people with night vision and eternal life. Enjoy reading their black background menu with tiny fonts in the darkness and then kick back while you wait for drinks (30 min) and food (1 hour, one dish cold) to glacially arrive. For the rest of us mere humans, it's miserable.

Beautiful and cozy restaurant. Went for a late brunch on a Saturday and order what you see in the picture: the croque madamme, tuna tartare and sides of wild mushrooms and sausages. Everything was very tasty and the service was great. As it was quite late for brunch we didn't have any problem to find a spot to sit inside. I also had a Bloody Mary that I loved. I'll be coming back!
Great food from Alsace, beautiful decor, good service even if a bit slow
Great food service is a bit slow but overall it's a very good restaurant and very nice stuff  From my French that loves baguette 🥖
Delicious dinner with excellent service.
Sitting here currently. Just finished my appetizer and cocktail. Both were amazing. This place has great atmosphere and flavor and it would take a lot for me to reduce my opinion at this point.

Pretty authentic Alsatian restaurant.   The steak tartare is chopped as it should be, not ground, and delightfully seasoned with Dijon mustard, capers, onions, etc.  Order some hand cut fries if they don't come with your order.
The wait staff is lovely. The brunch is delicious and the cocktails are stellar.
Service was a bit slow, but the food was excellent!! Very inventive mixes of flavors within all of the dishes. The flatbread and curry pasta were amazing. Met one of the owners, nice great.
Lovely food, beer and wines. What more could you ask for?
The best steak sandwich ever . French toasts are awesome and the staff are so friendly and cool .
Great menu. Love the onion soup!
Came here to meet up with my cousin. We sat by the street on a beautiful day. The food was amazing and so was the ambiance.

The place is cosy, quiet, well decorated and the food is great. 7 min away by walk from Carroll garden subway stop. Prices are not excessive at all. Great choice of wine. The service is also agreable. This place deserve to be recommanded.
Good food. Service was a little slow. Nice environment if you don't mind screaming kids
Absolutely delicious food and charming atmosphere. I never had food from Alsace region before and this was a really good introduction. The mix of French and German styles is awesome.
Great food & service. Nice atmosphere. Not bad prices for Brooklyn.

The place is cosy and warm in the winter, with a fireplace. But I am Alsatian myself and I was a little bit disappointed with the menu. Very little actual traditional courses offered, mostly stuff you'd find anywhere else. The tarte flambée had a nice thin crust but was on the soggy side  and lacked the usual fire wood taste. The salted pork was shredded too fine and was overly crispy. I was expecting at least some choucroute and baeckeoffe, warm comfort food.
Nice place, food not amazing
Great wine.
Combo of German and Trebuchet French, Alsatian goodies abound here. Loved the Chicken with curry (not Indian style). Spatzle was delicious, as was potato cake (not a dessert). Think 3"tall Latke.
Good food, but service was extremely slow/unorganized.  We ate here on holiday so maybe the regular staff had the day off?

Great little place.  Warm, welcoming.  Me and the wife had our 5 year anny here. Went for the smoke meats platter, mussels, fagra, tuna tartare.  Finished it off with filet mignon for me and she got the truffled pizza with Brie and something else. Superb. The filet was on point.  Medium... Not chewy, almost melted in your mouth... With fagra on top and sitting on potato pancake.  Seriously, telling all my friends about this... On second thought, probably shouldn't.

Meh. I grew up in this region, so I know Alsacien food can be amazing. Unfortunately I don't eat meat anymore, so couldn't try any tarte flambée, which has always been a favorite of mine. My husband's steak was far too overcooked for a French restaurant (he ordered medium and it was very, very well done) and one of the few vegetarian options I could have here was just so bland it was boring to eat. The setting is very nice and cozy, but the food just wasn't what I was hoping for.

I was quite disappointed with our Friday breakfast at this establishment.  I Googled breakfast spots in Downtown Brooklyn and this spot came up as a suggestion. Sure enough I looked up their menu and they had a decent breakfast/brunch menu. Here's where it goes wrong. On their website the "brunch" items are lumped into the same category as everything else so it's quite unclear that during the week they do not have a brunch menu.  We found that out when our waiter brought our menus and I see it's a lunch menu. When I asked him if they have breakfast items he said no. Well, we didn't want to waste our time and have to look for another spot so we skimmed the menu and ordered.  Note it was 11am and the restaurant was empty. We waited a while before he took our order. When he did come to our table we ordered coffee, salad Nicoise, steak frites and some wine. We ordered the steak medium rare. We got a medium well steak that was chewy, hard to cut and quite bland. The fries were OK. The salad was soaked in dressing. Literally so drenched, I couldn't finish it.  I really wanted something sweet to end this rather disasterous meal so I ordered the chocolate mousse. It barely passed as good. Some things look great in writing but when it comes to the table it's nothing like you imagine.  We finally are done and ask for the bill. Lo and behold, they charge us for refills on regular coffee. That really took the cake. I'm over this place and do not suggest going either. It's a true disappointment.
Niche fare done well.
If you like cheese and onion, you'll be set. So many delicious things.
Very good food, excellent drinks. Sometimes the service can be spotty but usually is good.

Definitely one of the best restaurant in the hood !!!  I've been there many times and I'v always had a great time. The staff is super friendly, they have a great menu with some french and Alsacien specialities and one of the best burger I ever had. I also love their cocktail creations and their wines from Alsace.  A must try if you are looking for good french food in Brooklyn !

An oasis in Cobble Hill!  We absolutely love La Cigogne.  The food is delicious whether it's brunch with the kids or dinner with friends there's something for even the fussiest palates.  The ambience is so inviting no matter what time of year - the cozy fire on freezing cold days or the cool terrace on warm summer evenings.  The staff are fantastic - so welcoming, attentive without being annoying and fun.

This is a wonderful French restaurant not far from my apartment. Their menu and cocktails seem to change with the season, never disappointing! During the winter I had mulled wine, brought me back to the time my husband and I were strolling around the Marché de Noël in France. Now that the weather is warm we enjoy having our tarte flambé out on the deck. I highly recommend The Chèvre its my favorite and always on the menu.

Wonderful restaurant, my experience was just perfect; if you want travel to the heart of France in just a visit and have some delicious authentic French cuisine this is the place to be. The staff is warm, professional and welcoming. Food is superbe and the wine selection is meticulously well made. I felt home and well taking care, can't wait to be back to try the rest of the menu...

Everytime I visit New York I have to stop at my favorite french restaurant . From the moment you arrive it's nothing but a pleasent experience . The staff is incredibly friendly. The place itself is impeccably clean. The food is amazing. The tarte flambee and the steak frites are my among my personal favorites. The fire place during the winter really adds to the relaxed warm ambience . I give it 5 stars .
Great ambience, great food! In a neighborhood with plenty of options, this French restaurant is the most laid back, authentic and fun with it's specials.
The Alsatian Mac & Cheese is to die for. Pair it with another side, you can't go wrong....
The best French restaurant in Brooklyn great location great food wonderful service and wonderful outdoor seating for beautiful spring days like today !

La Cigogne is a fantastic French restaurant that can host large parties or just simply have a romantic dinner for two. The beautifully designed cocktails and the homemade French cuisine makes for a wonderful experience. Their fireplace adds a nice touch for the chilly evenings to relax and enjoy the company of the regulars and staff. By the way, one of the best burgers in all the boroughs!
What a nice place ! I came at La Cigogne many times from the opening in June 2014, have never been desappointed & I can't wait to come again ! Excellent food & drinks, perfect & friendly service.
Charming ambiance. The food is good, but not outstanding.
Food was passable. The service was awful--very slow and unfriendly.

Stumbled upon this place in the neighborhood. Very unpretentious but still kinda fancy atmosphere. Nice mix of french and German (as the cuisine origin dictates) had a wonderful dinner with my boyfriend that was reasonably priced, generously portioned and DELICIOUS!

A very cozy and cute spot. I enjoyed my croque madame, the bread was fluffy and toasty - definitely al dente.. if that context makes sense. In addition, staff was great! I really enjoyed myself here, thinking of trying it out for dinner.
Great French draft beers. Amazing staff. Relaxing atmosphere that fits casual evenings with friends or more intimate/romantic dates.

So we were just in the neighborhood looking for some place to eat. This quaint restaurant was ideal, not just because of the low key but varied menu, and not just because their bartender actually knows how to make drinks, and not just because the food was delicious. The reason for my high rating is that the staff is marvelous. The owners obviously had some training in hospitality services and management. I love good service and great ambience. Qualifier... We went during the early dinner period (6:30)so it may be crazier later in the evening.
Must try!
I am French and I can tell you: this is really good French food!
A high quality menu and great mood indoors.
